<ns2440:para xmlns:ns2440="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.ejb.exceptions.introParagraph">

  All enterprise beans services accessed remotely (those specified in the home and remote
  interfaces) potentially throw <ns2441:literal xmlns:ns2441="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">java.rmi.RemoteException</ns2441:literal>. In addition
  enterprise bean may throw further exceptions. One differentiates in EJB systems between system
  and application level exceptions. These are handled differently by the application server.
</ns2440:para>